NOTE: I filmed this before the recent tragic Air India incident. As a frequent flier, the news really shook me â€” it still scares me, to be honest.

Flying from Mumbai to Bengaluru, I ended up reviewing dinner in economy class â€” both veg and non-veg meals â€” while also experiencing a little airline chaos before takeoff. From a surprise standby situation to clocking in my 10,000 steps at the airport, it was a journey even before boarding began!

Once in the air, the food service began and I was served two different meals. One had a spicy, comforting chicken curry; the other surprised me with a legit good dal makhani. And yes, I may have demolished the dessert entirely.

If youâ€™ve ever wondered what Air India serves on short-haul flights, or whether veg or non-veg wins â€” this oneâ€™s for you.
